<h1 id="what-is-niacinamide">What is Niacinamide?</h1>
<p>Niacinamide is also called nicotinamide, is one of the two major forms of vitamin B3 (niacin.It is most commonly found in supplements. Vitamin B3 is an essential neutrint for our body and its deficiency can lead us to several disorders of the skin, kidneys and brain. Hence, to prevent the deficiency of it, there are supplements of vitamin B3 available in the market.</p>

<h1 id="why-is-vitamin-b3-an-essntial-nutrient-for-the-body">Why is Vitamin B3 an essntial nutrient for the body?</h1>
<p>Cells in out body this Vitamin B3 (niacinamide), to make neccessary environment for keeping the cells functioning in our body to carry out various processes such as metabolism, damage repair etc.</p>

<p>There are a lot researches going on about this ingredient. However, the mechanism by which Vitamin B3 works in the skin is not indentified completely.</p>

<p>Despite of that, it has shown a lot of clinical benefits in the skin when applied topically.</p>

<p>Nowadays, it has been a promised active ingredient to help manage acne, rosacea, pigmentation issues, and wrinkles.</p>

<h1 id="what-is-it">What is it?</h1>
<p>As said earlier, it is a form of vitamin B3. It is water soluble and unlike <a href="https://www.sheenycare.com/what-is-ceramide/" target="_blank">ceramide</a>, our body doesn‚Äôt store it.</p>

<h1 id="who-needs-it">Who needs it?</h1>
<p><strong>All skin type</strong> needs niacinamide.</p>

